COVID-19 Status

As of 8:59PM PT yesterday, over 3.2 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 35 thousand have died.

In the last day, 9.3 thousand new infections were reported and 122 deaths. Currently 8,553 are in the hospital and 1,036 are in the ICU. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 79.3 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 5 years and older, 89% have their 1st shot and 83.2% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 7.1 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~47 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children under 5.

  • 80 in 100 have at least one vaccine dose,
    74 in 100 are fully vaccinated.
    34 in 100 have been boosted.
    Herd immunity is estimated at ~85%
